@Node 3 "The Problem!"

@{b}	The problem!!!@{ub}

E.R.S.98? Who you who do not know what E.R.S.98 is, E.R.S.98 is a
"software group" for the Amiga range of computers. E.R.S.98 was founded in
1993 by Sorg. It has silently existed since then with very few products.
Many who have been lost due to virus corruption. None who have been seriously
distributed. Not before the end of 1997 was E.R.S.98 truly active. Raven was
the first true demo release. So now we decided to go public with our stuff,
and distribute it via amongst other things Aminet. We have made as you might
know a diskmag called 'The Cracked Regular' which you are now reading a very
special edition of!!! But there where problems. Everything is now on the net
but all of the shit has one critical error! The e.mail address in which you
are supposed to contact us is wrong. Do not try to contact us via
ers@hotmail.com THIS IS THE WRONG E.MAIL ADDRESS!!!
If you want to contact us:
@{b}ersxx@hotmail.com@{ub} THIS IS THE RIGHT E.MAIL ADDRESS!!!

How can such an error have happened. By having fools to do your work for you.
I had limited internet access so I got O.J. to do the net. He was supposed to
get us a e.mail address and keep us informed on what mail we got and general
postmanship like that. But I should not have trusted him with such a daunting
task. He screwed up!!! Yes, I asked him what the e.mail address was.
ers@hotmail.com he said. But this is wrong, so a loth of the shit we released
on the net has the wrong e.mail address and right now I do not have the time
to update this. I doubt I will. But the first edition of our diskmag also
has this error. So anybody who wants to contribute will have to contribute to
another address. If you have sent e.mail to ers@hotmail.com, don't look at
me, I can not help you. You will either have to re send it or contact us and
we will try to trace your mail. We are currently trying to find out who the
hell has ers@hotmail.com as e.mail address but he/she has not responded jet.
If you are wondering why it took so long for our stuff to get out to Aminet,
this also is O.J.'s fault. As he was the net man he was supposed to upload
our stuff to Aminet. Yet another to difficult job. First he lost the
archives. I had to give him new. More products where made. The diskmag was
reaching the deadline. One of our contributors was supposed to mail his
contribution to ers@hotmail.com. O.J. could not find it (strange). He said
that Hotmail was down. I have just recently got internet access so I said
give me the password to ers@hotmail.com and I will take care of it. The
password was of course wrong. On this very day he says that I had
misunderstood the e.mail address was ers97@hotmail.com and he gave me a new
password. I checked it and this was of course oxcrap. So I had to get us a
new e.mail address more suiting: ersxx@hotmail.com. This reflects the
variable in E.R.S.98 quite fine. 

But I guess I can't stay mad at O.J. for long. I love that stinking bastard!

Always Sorg...
@EndNode

